commit.message: Update package version number.
Update setup.py and README for version 0.6.0.
Copy django.db.models.indexes.Index.hash_generator() into PartialIndex for compatibility.
Add Django 2.2 to Travis test matrix, make sure Python versions match what Django supports for each. Change all tests from TestCase to TransactionTestCase to make them work with recent SQLite.
Clean up after migrations tests.
Update version to 0.5.2
Test that partial_index.PF is imported directly, not from .query in migrations.
Introduce PF() as a compatibility wrapper for F() in Django 1.11.
Comment out DRF serializer tests - these are still TODO.

Make sure migrations import PartialIndex and PQ directly from the "partial_index" module, not submodules.
Add tests for makemigrations and migrate with partial indexes.
Attempt fixing description text in PyPI
Fix PyPI version badge link
Update version numbers to 0.5.0
Remove promises about DRF serializer validation.
Update Django minor versions in tests.
Add DRF serializer tests. They fail and are skipped for now.
Update future plans
Short example of text-based where-conditions in README, mention that they are deprecated.
Remove info on text-based where conditions from README. Add info on ValidatePartialUniqueMixin.

PQ - a compatibility class for Django 1.11 Q objects.
Tests now pass on Django 1.11.

Better Q-object to SQL where condition processing.
Added mixins.ValidatePartialUniqueMixin for model classes which are used in ModelForms or DRF Serializers.
Implementation for Q-object where-expressions for Django2.0. Includes support for using F-expressions in Q-expressions.
Tests for a PartialIndex that references multiple fields on the model.
runtest.py now allows --skip-postgresql or --skip-sqlite
Run travis tests on latest versions of Django 1.11 and 2.0
Minor readme edits
Documented release steps
Prepare README and setup.py for version 0.4.0.
Remove requirements.txt, instead use .travis.yml to set up test environments for various combinations of Python and Django versions.
Update PartialIndex.get_sql_create_template_values() for compatibility with Django 2.0.
